'''[[Opposition (parliamentary)|Opposition]]''' (16) *{{Color box|{{Lega Nord/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Lega Nord|LN]] (5) *{{Color box|#FFEB3B|border=darkgray}} [[Five Star Movement|M5S]] (4) *{{Color box|{{Forza Italia (2013)/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Forza Italia (2013)|FI]] (2) *{{Color box|{{Italian Left/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} Sì (2) *{{Color box|{{Brothers of Italy/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Brothers of Italy|FdI]] (1) *{{Color box|{{Other/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} Mixed (2) | last_election1 = [[Tuscan regional election, 2015|31 May 2015]] | next_election1 = [[2020 Tuscan regional election|31 May 2020]] | meeting_place = [[Palazzo Panciatichi, Florence|Palazzo Panciatichi]], [[Florence]] | website = [http://www.consiglio.regione.toscana.it/ Official website] }} {{Politics of Tuscany}} The '''Regional Council of Tuscany''' (''Consiglio Regionale della Toscana'') is the [[parliament|legislative assembly]] of [[Tuscany]].
It was first elected in 1970, when the [[Regions of Italy|ordinary regions]] were instituted, on the basis of the [[Constitution of Italy]] of 1948.
==Composition== The Regional Council of Tuscany was originally composed of 50 regional councillors. In the [[Tuscan regional election, 2005|2005 regional election]] the number of councillors increased to 65, while in the [[Tuscan regional election, 2010|2010 regional election]] it was reduced to 53.
Following the decree-law n. 138 of 13 August 2011 the number of regional councillors was reduced to 40, with an additional seat reserved for the President of the Region.
